<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.185100>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Fortiblatta cuspicolor Liang, Vršanský et Ren sp. nov. Daohugou, Inner Mongolia, China. Middle Jurassic (the Late Aalenian or Early Bajocian): 1 a. Line drawing of holotype (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 006); 1 b. Photograph of holotype (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 006)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/185100/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.185101>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Fortiblatta cuspicolor Liang, Vršanský et Ren sp. nov. Daohugou, Inner Mongolia, China. Middle Jurassic (the Late Aalenian or Early Bajocian): Line drawings. 2 a. Head (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 205); 2 b. P. mx, P. lb and Md. (CNU- B-NN- 2006 - 075); 2 c. Foreleg (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 075); 2 d. Midleg and Hindleg (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 258); 2 e. Ovipositor (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 217)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/185101/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.185103>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Fortiblatta cuspicolor Liang, Vršanský et Ren sp. nov. Daohugou, Inner Mongolia, China. Middle Jurassic (the Late Aalenian or Early Bajocian): 4 a. Mutual fusion of two veins (R) (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 009 RFW); 4 b. Fusion of vein to another vein (R-M) (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 070 RFW); 4 c. Lost of a branch (A) (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 073 - 1 LFW); 4 d. Unusual morphology (R) (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 072 LHW); 4 e. Unusual morphology (A) (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 073 - 1 RFW); 4 f. Unusual morphology (Rs-M and CuA) (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 261 RHW); 4 g. Unfinished of vein (M, and CuA) (CNU- B-NN- 2006 - 492 RFW); 4 h. Fused intercalary (CuA) (CNU-B-NN- 2006 - 007 LFW)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/185103/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

